President Obama issued a statement expressing his satisfaction with Congress passing the supplemental funding for Hurricane Sandy relief. He acknowledged the need for immediate aid and praised the bipartisan effort in making this happen. The President assured that his administration will continue to support the affected communities and work closely with state and local leaders to ensure the appropriate use of the funds. He highlighted that over $3 billion has already been provided for recovery efforts, including direct assistance to families and businesses. President Obama emphasized the ongoing commitment to rebuilding communities affected by the hurricane and stated that he will promptly sign the bill into law.